# Content Idea Finder — Questionnaire

This file configures the Content Idea Finder workflow. Copy it to
`content.md` in this same folder and the workflow will read your
answers from the `### Answer` blocks.

**On first run**, if a section is empty the workflow will ask you the
question. If you skip the question, it shows you the **built-in
defaults** and asks if you'd like to **add to**, **remove from**, or
**accept** that list — whatever you confirm becomes the saved answer.

**On re-run**, the agent asks per section whether to **keep**,
**append**, or **replace** the existing answer.

Free-form text is fine where the format allows it. For lists of
creators / queries, stick to the pipe-delimited format shown — those
are parsed directly, not by an LLM.

---

## Content Genres

**Question:** What topics do you want content ideas for? These drive
what trending signals the workflow treats as on-topic. One per line.

**Example answer:**
```
Startups
AI engineering
B2B SaaS
RevOps
```

**If you skip:** workflow uses the built-in default genre list and
prints it so you can react.

### Answer
<!-- agent writes here -->

