## Content Trend Queries

**Question:** What Twitter searches surface trending posts in your
space? One per line, format `bucket | query`. The bucket is just a
label so you can group queries by genre.

**Example answer:**
```
startups | seed funding announcement
ai | new LLM release
revops | sales forecasting tool
```

**If you skip:** workflow uses the 12-query default list in
`trend_queries.json`. It will print the list and let you add or
remove before saving.

### Answer
<!-- agent writes here -->

---

## Content HN Queries

**Question:** What Hacker News topics should we scan? One per line,
format `bucket | query | story_type | sort_by`. `story_type` is
`story` or `show_hn` (defaults to `story`). `sort_by` is `relevance`
or `date` (defaults to `relevance`).

**Example answer:**
```
ai_building | AI OR LLM OR agent | story | relevance
launches | Show HN | show_hn | date
```

**If you skip:** workflow uses the 4-bucket default list in
`hn_queries.json`. It will print the list and let you edit before
saving.

